==English==
===Etymology===
from '''Deolali''', a [[British]] [[army camp]] 100 miles north-east of [[Bombay]] where British soldiers would stay after finishing their [[tour of duty]], to await [[transport]] back to [[Britain]]; and [[tap]], a Persian or Urdu word for a [[malarial fever]] (ultimately from [[Sanskrit]] [[tapa]], meaning "heat" or "torment")
===Noun phrase===
'''[[doolally]] [[tap]]'''
# [[camp]] [[fever]]
# [[madness]], [[eccentricity]]
